  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but is actively fading on H4 at 44, a 56-point divergence flagged as the single most critical short-term signal, while CHF accelerates to H4 100 versus D1 33 and AUD surges to H4 70 versus D1 31, both confirming the regime shift away from USD dominance as S&P 500 at 7473 and Copper up 2.0% validate the macro overlay risk-on read. USDCHF is the cleanest expression of CHF acceleration against USD fading, and AUDUSD captures the AUD H4 surge, with AUDJPY and NZDJPY offering additional leverage as JPY D1 strength at 43 limits downside on the yen crosses.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nFed speak referencing terminal rate path hits USDJPY directly, a hawkish surprise reloads USD D1 dominance and invalidates the H4 fade setup.\nCopper extending above 6.50 triggers AUDUSD continuation through H4 resistance as commodity correlation reinforces AUD H4 CSM leadership at 70.\nUS-Iran talks producing a formal statement pressures WTI off 97, removing geopolitical bid and weakening USDCAD as CAD H4 CSM sits at zero floor.",
